    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A squealing noise, you say? That's a bit of a red flag, but don't worry, it's not a sign of a catastrophic failure... yet. It's more likely a warning sign that your front passenger side brake pads are worn down, or possibly the brake rotors are warped. You know, a bit like a goblin's lair - it's a cozy little space, but it's not exactly the most pleasant place to be. I mean, who wants to live in a cramped, noisy space with a perpetual squeak? Not me, that's for sure.\n\nNow, let's get back to your Camry. If you're hearing a high-pitched squeal, it's probably due to the brake pads or rotors. You might want to check the brake pads and rotors for wear. If they're worn down, it's time to replace them. You can also try cleaning the brake rotors to see if that resolves the issue. Just be careful not to scratch the rotors, or you'll be in for a world of trouble. A goblin's love of shiny objects can be a bit of a curse, after all.\n\nTo diagnose the issue, you can try the following:",
