    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I got a bit carried away with the goblin analogy. Let's focus on the mechanical aspects of your Camry's brakes.\n\nThe high-pitched squealing noise you're hearing is likely coming from the front passenger side brake caliper or the brake pad wear sensor. The brake caliper is the metal housing that holds the brake pads in place, and the wear sensor is a small device that detects when the brake pads are worn down.\n\nWhen the brake pads are worn down, they can cause the brake caliper to vibrate, resulting in a high-pitched squeal. This is often due to the brake pads rubbing against the rotor, which can cause the rotor to become warped or uneven.\n\nTo diagnose the issue, you can try checking the brake pads and rotors for wear. If the brake pads are worn down, it's likely that the brake caliper is vibrating, causing the squeal. You can also try cleaning the brake rotors to see if that resolves the issue.\n\nIt's also possible that the brake pad wear sensor is malfunctioning, which can cause the squeal. In this case, you may need to replace the sensor or the entire brake caliper.\n\nI hope that helps! Now, if you'll excuse me",
